race.comment: MEGHAN (4) is putting together some solid results. Just missed here then scored by 5 lengths as public elect over 1400m at Cloncurry. Has a handy 2kg claim today and will take some stopping. SHOALWATER BAY (1) was only beaten 2.2L at Mackay, then improved last time out to score by 1.3L as favourite over 1600m at Barcaldine. The 2kg claimer has a wide gate to manage, but the gelding is suited in this lineup and will go close with average luck in the run. MIDORI FOREST (8) raced on the speed and kept going to deliver his Maiden over 1200m at this track, as expected. He's lightly raced with plenty of scope for improvement. LEGAL CHALLENGE (10) is capable of his day and this is easier than Townsville. He may be the best of the remainder.
